               <history>
                  
                  <origin notBefore="1650" notAfter="1699" cert="medium" evidence="external">
                     <p>The manuscript was written in
                        <origPlace key="DK">Denmark</origPlace>. <bibl>Kålund, <ref
                           type="secondary-1" target="KKKat">Katalog</ref><biblScope
                              type="volume">I</biblScope><biblScope type="pages"
                                 >365</biblScope></bibl> dates it to the <date
                                    notBefore="1600" notAfter="1699">17th
                                    century</date>.</p>
                     <p>Narrower dating information is provided by
                        <bibl>Schlyter: <ref target="CorpJur9">Corpus juris Sveo-Gotorum antiqui: Codex juris Scanici</ref><biblScope
                           type="volume">IX</biblScope><biblScope type="pages"
                              >xcix</biblScope></bibl>, who dates it to the <origDate
                                 notBefore="1650" notAfter="1699">later half of the 17th
                                 century</origDate>.</p>
                  </origin>
                  <provenance>
                     <p>At some point part of a larger manuscript, later divided into two units: AM 38 a 4to and <ref target="AM04-0038-b">AM 38 b 4to</ref>.</p>
                     <p>Number <q>38 in 4to</q> was recorded in <name type="person" key="JonOla003">Jón Ólafsson</name>'s catalogue (1730) as one manusript, 
                        but there is no indication of two copies.</p>
                  </provenance>
               </history>
